<h2>Pre-The Force Awakens</h2>

<p>Since the end of Revenge of the Sith in [date] Star Wars didn't go away completly. Books, comics, and tv shows were still made. [Give examples of each respectively]. <br _> <br _>

In May of 2011 George met and talked with Disneys Bob Iger about retiring and selling both Lucasfilm and the Star Wars franchise.[Insert picture of meeting] <br _><br _>

Then on October 30 2012 Disney announced their deal to acquire Lucasfilm for 4.05 billion (half cash, half disney stock).[Insert disney vader picture] Kathleen Kennedy, now the president of Lucasfilm would head brand managment and act as producer for all future films.<br _><br _>

On April 24 2014 Lucasfilm announced that all prior expanded universe(EU) material would be considered non canon. With the destruction of the old EU Lucasfilm stated that all old canon would be branded as "Legends" and that future canan material may draw apon it for future works. In addition to this on January 3rd 2014 Lucasfilm also announced that Dark Horse Comics would no longer hold its license and all subsequent comics would be published through Marvel Comics. Books would also be published under Del Rey and would release on a bi-monthly schedule.<br _><br _></p>

